# t/probe/ui-request.test — ring 3 (docs/13): does a REAL agent raise a valid web
# UI request? The answer→resume machinery is deterministic and covered offline by
# t/research/ui-request*.test; this probe validates only the reality-dependent part
# — that a real Claude agent, told to collect input it must not put in an email,
# chooses the form channel and writes a request.json that mints a working link.
# One agent turn, so it is cheap.
#
# Run it live (real Claude + Fastmail), recording the real turn as a cassette:
#     ./bin/kasi probe t/probe/ui-request.test
# In --ring sim (the merge gate) the agent block below scripts the turn from the
# real captured spec; in --ring live the real agent runs and the assertions must
# hold for WHATEVER spec it writes. To fold the captured real turn into the offline
# recorded gate, move this file to t/recorded/ once its cassette exists.

# A plus-addressed initiator, not käsi's own identity: with reply-from kasi@decode.ee
# below, a bare-self sender is now dropped (SEV1 self-reply loop, decision-016).
# kasi+probe@decode.ee is not "self" to SameAddress yet still käsi's own mailbox, so a
# live probe's reply stays self-contained.
send allow-sender    { address kasi+probe@decode.ee }
send set-reply-from  { address kasi@decode.ee }

deliver {
    from    kasi+probe@decode.ee
    to      research@kasi.test
    subject "show me your web form"
    body    "I'd like to try your secure web form. Please raise a UI request that collects a few fields — include at least a text field, a choice, a file upload, and a secret (an API key) — then stop; I'll fill it in from the link. Do not ask for any of these in your reply."
}

task 1 status is awaiting-agent

# Ring 1/2 script the turn from the real captured spec; ring 3 runs the real agent.
agent {
    out request.json [fixture ui-request/live-sample.json]
    out reply.txt "Here's a secure form with one of each field type — use the link to fill it in."
}

task 1 status is awaiting-user

# Robust to whatever the real agent writes: it chose the form channel (the reply
# carries the capability link) and the request registered with a link.
outbound last body matches "*provide the requested input*"
task 1 request-link matches "*/requests/*"
